  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study aims at evaluating the AirGoTM system's performance, as compared to standard
      pulmonary function tests.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Primary endpoint:

      â€¢ To test the AirGoTM system's respiratory rate recording accuracy at rest and during
      physical exercise, as compared to standard tests.

      Secondary endpoints:

        -  To test the accuracy of the AirGoTM system's derived respiratory parameters (tidal
           volume, minute ventilation, Tiffeneau-Pinelli index, FEV1 and VO2max) at rest and during
           physical exercise, as compared to standard tests.

        -  To test comfort and subjects' compliance with the AirGoTM system during long term
           recording (24 hours).
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
